sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Gateway
    participant Auth as Auth Middleware<br/>Bearer Token (SHA-256)
    participant API as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Engine as AsyncLLM Engine
    participant CPU as PyTorch CPU Backend<br/>C++ Kernels
    participant PVC as Local Storage / PVC
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over PVC, HF: Flow 3: Model Loading (startup)
    Engine->>PVC: Load model weights (File I/O)
    PVC-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    opt HF_HUB_OFFLINE=0
        Engine->>HF: Download model (HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, HF Token)
        HF-->>Engine: Model weights
    end

    Note over Client, CPU: Flow 1: OpenAI Chat Completion Request
    Client->>Auth: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 8000/TCP<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>
    Auth->>Auth: SHA-256 compare token
    Auth->>API: Authenticated request
    API->>Engine: Process inference (in-process)
    Engine->>CPU: Tensor computation (in-process)
    CPU-->>Engine: Computed tokens
    Engine-->>API: Generated tokens (streaming)
    API-->>Client: SSE stream response<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 8000/TCP

    participant Router as llm-d Rust Router
    participant GRPC as vLLM gRPC Server<br/>50051/TCP gRPC/HTTP2

    Note over Router, CPU: Flow 2: gRPC Generation (llm-d Router)
    Router->>GRPC: Generate RPC (gRPC/HTTP2, 50051/TCP, plaintext)
    GRPC->>Engine: Process inference (in-process)
    Engine->>CPU: Tensor computation (in-process)
    CPU-->>Engine: Computed tokens
    Engine-->>GRPC: Token stream
    GRPC-->>Router: Streaming response (gRPC/HTTP2, plaintext)
